definition.value: Catalysis of the reactions -  chloral hydrate -eq- 3 H+ + 2 e- + trichloroacetate, and chloral hydrate + H2 -eq- H2O + trichloroethanol.

Catalysis of the reaction -  1-chloro-2,2-bis(4-chlorophenyl)ethene + 2 H+ + 2 e- -eq- 1-chloro-2,2-bis(4-chlorophenyl)ethane. 1-chloro-2,2-bis(4-chlorophenyl)ethene is also known as DDMU -  1-chloro-2,2-bis(4-chlorophenyl)ethane is also known as DDMS.
